  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted covering inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid viscosity; results confirmed low sensitivity of the relative hemolysis index to these parameters across the five operating points examined.",
